President Obama spoke with Mexican President Calderón to express the United States' support for Mexico's efforts to combat organized crime. They discussed the recent operation in Matamoros against Gulf Cartel leader Antonio Cárdenas Guillén, known as Tony Tormenta, in which Cárdenas Guillén died. President Obama offered his condolences for the Mexican officials and journalist who lost their lives in the operation. He also thanked President Calderón for working closely with US officials to ensure the safety of American citizens in Matamoros. The President emphasized his commitment to strengthening the security partnership between the US and Mexico.